RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY MILE RACE 1 7F Dirt CR: 91. Claiming Purse 15500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race In 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500. Alberta Bred Claiming Price $16,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: THE BEAT got away alertly, cleared the field and shifted in to set the pace, soon faced pressure from an outside foe, was challenged turning for home, kicked clear in upper stretch and held safe. BORKAN lacked room in behind the leader and eventual winner and was put to a firm hold by the rider early, lost ground heading into the turn, swung out for the drive, was gaining but too late. GIVE EM HECK BECK pressed the eventual winner from between runners coming the five-eighths, dueled late on the turn, flattened out in the stretch. BODYMOOR HEATH was forwardly-placed stalking from outside, began to weaken at the three-eighths traveling three wide, faded in the lane. CHROME KING was outpaced, swung five to six wide for the stretch run and was never near enough to threaten.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Journal H. CENTURY MILE RACE 5 6F Dirt CR: 98. Stakes Purse 50000. A BLACK TYPE HANDICAP STAKE FOR THREE-YEAR-OLDS AND UPWARD. A fee of $100.00 required to nominate. The purse will be divided $30,000 to the owner of the winner, $10,000 to the second place finisher, $5,000 to the third place finisher, $2,500 to the fourth place finisher and $1,000 to the fifth place finisher. RACE.FOOTNOTES: FOREVER LADY steadied on heels when placed in tight quarters past the five-eighths, settled back into stride and advanced inside early on the turn, was held up in behind coming to the quarter pole, bid up the rail in upper stretch, drew clear and was kept to the task. SASSY CINDERELLA stalked within range, went four wide on the turn, bid at the quarter pole, had a narrow and brief lead in upper stretch, was no match for the winner but held the place. WILD RUNNIN MAGGIE shifted in two to three wide early, dropped back heading into the turn, angled out past the three-sixteenths, kept on late to get show honors while missing second. SAYGE'S SPIRIT was forced in coming past the five-eighths by a rival, altered outside that foe at that juncture, was ridden along chasing in behind while off the inside, was forced out in upper stretch and ran on. JELLI broke outwardly, raced toward the back while off the inside, improved position in the stretch. SUBLIME EUPHORIA broke inwardly, was urged forward inside to the lead after three-sixteenths, set the pace into the turn coming off the rail a bit, weakened in the stretch. MIDNIGHT TAKE was outpaced and made no bid racing outside. ANNA'S IMAGE was never a threat racing off the inside. FOLLOWING A STEWARDS' INQUIRY INTO THE STRETCH NO ACTION WAS TAKEN.
